comments.body:
I was able to reproduce the issue and get into the broken event state following those steps:

1) Create a new project. Open "Run configuration" and run it using iOS SDK 7.0, Simulator version 7.0 and Display Type "Non-Retina".
Result: iOS 7 Retina simulator is opening. Everything works fine as expected.

2) After point 1, "Run configuration" and run the project using iOS SDK 7.0, Simulator version 6.1 and Display Type "Non-Retina".
Result: iOS 6.1 Simulator opens and everything works fine as expected.

3) After point 2, 'Run configuration" and run the project using iOS SDK 7.0, Simulator version 7.0 and Display Type "Non-Retina".
Result: iOS 6.1 Simulator is being opened instead of the 7.0. In this states, all events are not diplayed in console.

For example, something like:
{code}
var win1 = Titanium.UI.createWindow({  
    title:'Tab 1',
    backgroundColor:'#fff'
});
var tab1 = Titanium.UI.createTab({  
    icon:'KS_nav_views.png',
    title:'Tab 1',
    window:win1
});

var label1 = Titanium.UI.createLabel({
	color:'#999',
	text:'I am Window 1',
	font:{fontSize:20,fontFamily:'Helvetica Neue'},
	textAlign:'center',
	width:'auto'
});

label1.addEventListener('click', function(){
	Ti.API.info('#### logging event');
	console.log('#### console log');
});

win1.add(label1);

win1.open();

{code}

clicking on the 'label1' when the simulator is in this state does not produce any output in the console log.

Closing ticket as fixed. Verified application logging appears on iOS 7 simulator with Alloy and Classic app. In the default Alloy app, added this code in index.js to verify:
{code}
function doClick(e) {
    alert($.label.text);
    
    Ti.API.trace('#### monkey trace');
    Ti.API.debug('#### monkey debug');
    Ti.API.info('#### monkey info');
    Ti.API.warn('#### monkey warn');
    Ti.API.error('#### monkey error');
	
    console.log('#### monkey console');
}
{code}

And in the default Classic app, added this code in app.js to verify:
{code}
label1.addEventListener('click', function(e){
	Ti.API.trace('#### monkey trace');
    Ti.API.debug('#### monkey debug');
    Ti.API.info('#### monkey info');
    Ti.API.warn('#### monkey warn');
    Ti.API.error('#### monkey error');
	
    console.log('#### monkey console');
});
{code}

Tested on:

Appcelerator Studio, build: 3.2.1.201402061120
SDK build: 3.2.2.v20140214120903, 3.3.0.v20140214150951 
CLI: 3.2.1
Alloy: 1.3.1
Xcode: 5.0.2, 5.1 beta 5
Devices: iphone retina 3.5 inch simulator (7.0.3, 7.1), ipad retina simulator (7.0.3, 7.1)
